timothy sorg stanford department of classics skip to navigation department of classics standford university logo header home people programs courses projects news events resources contact timothy sorg contact information timsorg stanford edu biography tim graduated with a master's degree in ancient history in 2011 and now studies in the doctoral program in classics at cornell university he received is ba in history and philosophy in 2010 from oregon state university honors college his undergraduate thesis was titled the end of the mycenaean palatial civilization a study of greek dark age historiography his interests include the intersections of rhetoric citizenship and democracy in classical athens and the emergence of archaic greece from the greek dark age email stanford classics find us on facebook address & phone search upcoming events alicia jimenez original copy imitation and colonialism in roman hispania 02 16 2012 see more site info 2012 stanford university department of classics all rights reserved site design by chapter three login login with sunet speaker request webform for faculty stanford classics wikisite powered by drupal an open source content management system
